<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="132" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="25.[193,1404,712,1808]" pageId="25" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[195,543,1579,1612]" pageId="25" pageNumber="132">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Ethiopian Highland Hare is considered to be abundant within its Ethiopian distribution. No data are available on its population status, and conservation threats are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
